Chamber Comments on New California High Speed Rail Business Plan..\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n                        <h3>Special Chamber Programs</h3>\r\n\r\n                        <h5>Redwood City, Belmont, Menlo Park, San Carlos Leadership Program</h5>\r\n\r\n                        <p class=\"p1\">Learn how The Redwood City San Mateo County Chamber of Commerce is helping to educate local leaders with the <a href=\"redwood-city-belmont-san-carlos-leadership-program.php\">Redwood City, Belmont, Menlo Park, San Carlos Leadership program.</a></p>\r\n\r\n                        <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n                        \r\n\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n                  <div class=\"col-2\">\r\n\r\n                   	<p><a href=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/4page-img2.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/4page-img2.jpg\" alt=\"4page-img2\" width=\"296\" height=\"130\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n                     <strong>The Mission of the Chamber</strong> \r\n\r\n                     <p>The mission of the Redwood City, San Mateo County  Chamber of Commerce is to promote economic prosperity  for our community through business representation and  advocacy with emphasis on information,communication  and education.</p>\r\n\r\n                        <h3>Chamber Committees</h3>\r\n\r\n                        <p class=\"p1\"><strong>Transportation &amp; Housing Committee</strong> - Monitors and evaluates transportation system and housing issues. (2nd Thursday, at Noon)</p>\r\n\r\n                        <p class=\"p1\"><strong>Governmental Relations Committee</strong> - Studies and speaks out on all government activities that affect local business. (3rd Wednesday, at Noon) </p>\r\n\r\n                        <p class=\"p1\"><strong>Education Committee</strong> - Working in conjunction with local educational institutions to determine ways in which business can participate to improve community schools. (1st Wednesday, at Noon)</p>\r\n\r\n                        <p class=\"p1\"><strong>Economic Development Committee</strong> - Develops and implements plans to attract and retain commercial and industrial development in Redwood City and San Mateo County. (1st Tuesday, at Noon)</p>\r\n\r\n                        <p class=\"p1\"><strong><a href=\"redwood-city-chamber-ambassadors.php\">Ambassadors Committee</a></strong> - Serves as a liaison to the Chamber\'s membership. Attends networking mixers, ribbon cuttings and grand openings. (1st Monday, at Noon)</p>\r\n\r\n                        <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n                        \r\n\r\n                        \r\n\r\n                        \r\n\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n                  <div class=\"col-3\">\r\n\r\n                   	<p><a href=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/jointhechamber.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/jointhechamber.jpg\" alt=\"jointhechamber\" width=\"296\" height=\"130\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n                     <strong>Joining the Chamber</strong>\r\n\r\n                     <p>If you are looking to network with local business, be part of the Redwood City community, or learn about the issues concerning local business in Redwood City - that you need to <a href=\"redwood-city-chamber-membership.php\">Join the Redwood City San Mateo County Chamber of Commerce</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n                        <h3>Member Directory</h3>\r\n\r\n                        <p class=\"p1\">Visit the <a href=\"chamberdirectory/index.php\">Redwood City San Mateo County Chamber of Commerce membership directory</a> and support our local businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n                        <h3>The Redwood City San Mateo County Chamber of Commerce Board</h3>\r\n\r\n                        <p class=\"p1\">Meet the <a href=\"redwood-city-chamber-board.php\">Redwood City San Mateo County Board of Directors </a>as well as the Staff of the Redwood City San Mateo County Chamber of Commerce</p>\r\n\r\n                        <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n                    </div>','About Us','','publish','closed','open','','about-us','','','2013-06-28 03:03:51','2013-06-27 20:03:51','',0,'http://rwcc.wpengine.com/?page_id=48',0,'page','',0),(49,2,'2013-06-28 02:52:11','2013-06-27 19:52:11','<div class=\"col-1\">\r\n\r\n                     	<p><a href=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/ariel-rwc.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/ariel-rwc.jpg\" alt=\"ariel rwc\" width=\"296\" height=\"130\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n                        <strong>Local &amp; Regional Government</strong> \r\n\r\n                        <p><a href=\"redwood-city-city-council.php\">Redwood City City Council</a><br>\r\n\r\n                          <a href=\"san-mateo-county-board-of-supervisors.php\">San Mateo County Board of Supervisors</a><br>\r\n\r\n                        <a href=\"state-of-california-legslators.php\">State of California Legislators</a></p>\r\n\r\n                        <p>Got Questions on how to contact your local legislator? Here are Tips and Protocol\'s when <a href=\"contacting-your-legislators-protocol.php\">writing to your local legislator</a>.<br>\r\n\r\n                        </p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n                     <div class=\"col-2\">\r\n\r\n                     	<p><a href=\"redwood-city-san-mateo-county-schools.php\"><a href=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/schools.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/schools.jpg\" alt=\"schools\" width=\"296\" height=\"130\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-66\" /></a></a></p>\r\n\r\n                        <strong>The Schools &amp; Colleges of Redwood City &amp; San Mateo County</strong> \r\n\r\n                        <p>The <span id=\"lw_1264807429_1\"><a href=\"redwood-city-san-mateo-county-schools.php\">Redwood City School District</a></span> aims to be a premier California School. <span id=\"lw_1264807429_2\">The District</span> serves nearly 9,000 elementary and <span id=\"lw_1264807429_3\">middle school students</span> at 17 schools in the <span id=\"lw_1264807429_4\">Redwood City</span>, <span id=\"lw_1264807429_5\">San Carlos</span>,  Atherton and Menlo Park. The District is committed to the success of  each and every student, and takes its Board-adopted mission seriously;  educating every child for success.<br>\r\n\r\n                          \r\n\r\n                       </p>\r\n\r\n                     </div>\r\n\r\n                     <div class=\"col-3\">\r\n\r\n                     	<p><a href=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/cityofredwoodcity.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/cityofredwoodcity.jpg\" alt=\"cityofredwoodcity\" width=\"296\" height=\"130\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-68\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n                        <strong>Redwood City Information</strong> \r\n\r\n                        <p>The City is located in the Bay Area 25 miles south of San Francisco and 25 miles north of San Jose. <a href=\"the-city-of-redwood-city.php\">Redwood City</a> is home to approximately 76,000 people. It is the oldest bayside city in San Mateo County, incorporated in 1867, and has been the County Seat since 1856. </p>\r\n\r\n                        <p><a href=\"redwood-city-phone-numbers.php\">Redwood City Emergency Phone Numbers<br></a>\r\n\r\n                         <!--  <a href=\"doing-business-in-redwood-city.php\">Doing Business in Redwood City</a><br /> -->\r\n\r\n                        <a href=\"chamberdirectory/index.php\">Redwood City Business Directory </a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n                     </div>','Community','','publish','closed','open','','community','','','2013-06-28 03:16:16','2013-06-27 20:16:16','',0,'http://rwcc.wpengine.com/?page_id=49',0,'page','',0),(50,2,'2013-06-28 02:52:27','2013-06-27 19:52:27','                        <p align=\"center\"><object width=\"400\" height=\"267\"><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\"><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=7729196&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=00adef&amp;fullscreen=1\"><embed src=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=7729196&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=00adef&amp;fullscreen=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" width=\"400\" height=\"267\"></object></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n                      \r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n                     <div class=\"row-2\">\r\n\r\n                     	<div class=\"wrapper\">\r\n\r\n                        	<div class=\"col-1\">\r\n\r\n                           	<h3>Our Mission &amp; Vision</h3>\r\n\r\n                              <p class=\"p1\"><strong>Our Mission Statement </strong><br>\r\n\r\nThe Mission of the Redwood City-San Mateo County Chamber of Commerce is to promote economic\r\n\r\nprosperity for our community through business representation and advocacy with\r\n\r\nemphasis on information, communication and education.</p> \r\n\r\n                              \r\n\r\n                              <p class=\"p1\"><strong>Vision Statement</strong><br>\r\n\r\nBy 2015, the Redwood City San Mateo County Chamber of Commerce will be the leading influential\r\n\r\norganization driving the economic, public policy and quality of life issues facing our community.</p> \r\n\r\n                              \r\n\r\n                           </div>\r\n\r\n                           <div class=\"col-2\">\r\n\r\n                           	<h3>Other Chamber Benefits</h3>\r\n\r\n                             <ul type=\"disc\">\r\n\r\n                              <li>•Eligibility for Credit Union Membership either with San Mateo Credit Union or Provident Credit Union.</li>\r\n\r\n                             \r\n\r\n                                <li>•Online Newsletter.</li>\r\n\r\n                                <li>•Candidates Forum.</li>\r\n\r\n                                <li>•Economic Forecast</li>\r\n\r\n                                <li>•Legislative       representation on local &amp; state level.</li>\r\n\r\n                                \r\n\r\n                                <li>•Brochures on <a href=\"the-city-of-redwood-city.php\">Redwood       City</a> and the area. </li>\r\n\r\n                                   <li>•Business referrals       (members only). </li>\r\n\r\n                                   <li>•Resource for       statistical and demographic data.</li>\r\n\r\n                             </ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"p1\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n                              <p class=\"alignright p3\"><a href=\"http://www.redwoodcitychamber.com/ecom/index.php?p=product&amp;id=3&amp;parent=2\" target=\"_blank\">Join the Chamber Today&gt;&gt;</a></p></div></div>','Membership','','publish','closed','open','','membership','','','2013-06-28 05:59:21','2013-06-27 22:59:21','',0,'http://rwcc.wpengine.com/?page_id=50',0,'page','',0),(51,2,'2013-06-28 02:52:40','2013-06-27 19:52:40','','Contact','','publish','closed','open','','contact','','','2013-06-28 02:52:40','2013-06-27 19:52:40','',0,'http://rwcc.wpengine.com/?page_id=51',0,'page','',0),(52,2,'2013-06-28 02:52:54','2013-06-27 19:52:54','<a href=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/leadership-2010.jpg\"><img style=\"float:left;\" src=\"http://rwcc.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/leadership-2010.jpg\" alt=\"leadership-2010\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-69\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Developing Leaders For Our Community’s Future</strong></p>\r\n\r\n                       <p>In dynamic sessions held one Friday a month, September  through June, participants learn about issues of vital concern to their city;  and learn how they can effectively shape the future of their community, their  organization or their business.&nbsp; The  focus of each session is not on specific political viewpoints; rather, a number  of alternative views are presented from experts in the given areas.<br>\r\n\r\n                         Sessions generally run from 8am until 3pm.&nbsp; A continental breakfast and lunch are  provided.</p>\r\n\r\n                       <p>  <strong>Applications</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                         We invite those  individuals seeking to challenge themselves by becoming more educated and  involved in their community.&nbsp; <br>\r\n\r\n                         Enrollment is limited to 40 individuals.&nbsp;Completed applications are due back to the Chamber no later than Friday, August 30th, 2013<br>\r\n\r\n  <strong>Tuition</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                         Tuition for the program is $1,000.00, due by the first class day.<br>\r\n\r\n  <strong>Attendance</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                         Class members must not miss more than 2 classes to graduate  from program.</p>\r\n\r\n                       <div class=\"alignright\"><a href=\"apply-redwood-city-leadership-program.php\" class=\"link1\">Apply Now For the 2013-2014 Class</a></div>\r\n\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n                      <div class=\"wrapper\">\r\n\r\n                        <h3>Key Program Dates</h3>\r\n\r\n                        <p> Leadership classes are the 2nd Friday of each month from \r\n\r\n8:00am – 3:00pm. \r\n\r\nLocations vary each month\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n                        	<ul class=\"list2 col-1\">\r\n\r\n                           	\r\n\r\n                        	  <li>\r\n\r\n                        	    <p><strong>September 13, 2013</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                        	      Program Orientation</p>\r\n\r\n                                <p><strong>October 11, 2013</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                                  Leadership  Retreat</p>\r\n\r\n                                <p><strong>November 1, 2013(1st Friday)</strong><br>\r\n                                Public Safety Day</p>\r\n\r\n                                <p><strong>December 13, 2013</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                                  Housing &amp; Transportation</p>\r\n\r\n                                <p><strong>January 10, 2014</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                                  Education</p>\r\n\r\n                                <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n                              <li></li>\r\n\r\n                           </ul>\r\n\r\n                         <ul class=\"list2 col-2\">\r\n\r\n                   	       <li>\r\n\r\n                       	       <p><strong>February 7, 2014 (1st Friday)</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                       	         Economics  &amp; Business</p>\r\n\r\n                               <p><strong>March 14, 2014</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                                 City  &amp; County Government</p>\r\n\r\n                               <p><strong>April 18, 2014</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                                 Sustainable Communities</p>\r\n\r\n                               <p><strong>May 9, 2014</strong><br>\r\n\r\n                                 Health  Care Day</p>\r\n\r\n                               <p><strong>June 13, 2014 </strong><br>\r\n\r\n                                 Civic  Engagement/Graduation</p>\r\n\r\n                   	       </li>\r\n\r\n                        </ul>','Leadership','','publish','closed','open','','leadership','','','2013-06-28 06:16:01','2013-06-27 23:16:01','',0,'http://rwcc.wpengine.com/?page_id=52',0,'page','',0),(53,2,'2013-06-28 02:54:51','2013-06-27 19:54:51',' ','','','publish','closed','open','','53','','','2013-06-28 02:55:24','2013-06-27 19:55:24','',0,'http://rwcc.wpengine.com/?p=